bio:
Luigi Rizzo is Associate Professor in Sanitary and Environmental Engineering at the Department of Civil Engineering, University of Salerno (Italy).He is:

• Coordinator of the "International PhD School on Advanced Oxidation Processes";
• Editor of "Journal of Environmental Chemical Engineering" (Elsevier) since 2022;
• Co-founder and President of the AOP4Water spin-off of the University of Salerno;
• He was Chair of the EAAOP-7 conference, 10-13 June 2024, Paestum-Capaccio (SA), Italy.

He was/is principal investigator (26) and investigator (13) in 21 national and 18 international research projects. He supervised 6 post-doc (2 visiting), 16 PhD students (7 visiting), 61 MSc students (12 visiting) and 3 undergraduate students. His main research interest is water/wastewater treatment and disinfection by advanced oxidation processes. He is (co-)author of 179 papers, 135 in “peer review indexed journals” (101 in Q1 journals), with 12.531 citations and 51 h-index (SCOPUS database, July 10th, 2025). He is among the “Top 100.000 scientists” according to the so called Stanford’s rank (he was ranked 82nd (out of 77304) for the category Environmental Science in 2020).
